ce:section.ce:para:
Mixing a certain concentration of N@C-dots (1.0 mg/mL) with specific IC concentration in B.R. buffer (pH 3.0) generates a cyan blue colored product accompanied by the appearance of a new peak at 627 nm. The impact of color and the intensity of peak progressively increase by IC concentration increment, which has explained by the ion-pairing mechanism. The calibration graphs obtained by plotting the absorbance values against IC concentration at λmax 627 and were found to be linear over the concentration range of 9.97 – 80.0 µM (Fig. 6
                        ), with regression equation of A = 0.02CIC
                         − 0.0143, (R2 = 0.9986 and LOD = 3.3 µM) where (A) is the absorbance, (c) is the concentration μM, R2 = correlation coefficient, and LOD = limit of detection.
